<p>Now we've got the proper failure: there is no link called <code>Delete</code>.</p>
<p>Let's code for this! Remember, do as little work as possible.</p>
<h2 id="coding-the-delete">Coding the Delete <a class="headerlink" href="complex-delete#coding-the-delete" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Add a new <code>deleteAction()</code> and a route of <code>/admin/products/delete/{id}</code>. Name
it <code>product_delete</code>. We could get fancy and add an <code>@Method</code> annotation that say
that this will only match <code>POST</code> or <code>DELETE</code> requests. Let's keep it simple for now:</p>
